body:
### Describe the solution you'd like

It would be helpful to be able to see the Temporal services, their metadata (such as IP) and the dynamic configuration that are applied to them.


An example of the output follow the Temporal CLI output might look like:
```json
{  
    "frontend": {
        "127.0.0.10": {
            "rps": 2400,
            "persistenceMaxQPS": 2000
        },
        "127.0.0.11": {
            "rps": 2400,
            "persistenceMaxQPS": 3000
        },
    },
    "history": {
        "127.0.0.12": {
            "rps": 3000,
            "persistenceMaxQPS": 9000
        },
        "127.0.0.13": {
            "rps": 6000,
            "persistenceMaxQPS": 18000
        },
    }
}
```

### Additional context

This deserves to be a part of the CLI because it is information that operators would benefit from having up-front rather than needing to dig into from configuration files / container environment variables. 

Since dynamic configuration can be modified on a per service bases, this makes managing at scale difficult and prone to error.
